307
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:04,800
也没提我们的东境防御系统
Nothing on our defence system on the Eastern Frontier.

308
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,440
要塞 地堡 碉堡都没提到
No forts, no bunkers, no pillboxes.

309
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:10,440
确实如此 这也证实了我们最担心的事
Exactly. It confirms what we feared most.

310
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:14,880
他们开着坦克穿过比利时森林而来
They're coming with tanks through the Belgian forests.

311
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,400
我想这些应该能说服那些不相信的人
Well, this should persuade the unbelievers.

312
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,680
这下我们能应对他们了
Now we'll be ready for them.

313
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:22,360
Jean-Francois 干得漂亮
You've done well, Jean-Francois.

314
00:26:22,360 --> 00:26:23,844
我已经举荐你
I've recommended that you

315
00:26:23,845 --> 00:26:26,280
去总参谋部工作了
take up a position here in General Staff.

316
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:28,920
我待在华沙已经没有任何意义了
There's nothing to keep me in Warsaw anymore.

317
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:32,440
谢谢你 长官
Thank you, sir.

318
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:53,000
- 你好   - 可把你盼来了
- Hello.- Finally!

319
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:55,160
我老哥的热情造访
A visit from my big brother!

320
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,240
热烈欢迎
Welcome.

321
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:06,240
你在这儿干了多久了
How long have you worked here?

322
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,720
有一阵了
A while now.

323
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:13,240
Etienne也有对私人客户的古董业务
Etienne also deals in art for private clients.

324
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:16,480
我可以帮你找些精美绝伦的宝贝装点宅邸
I could find you something vibrant and cheerful for the estate.

325
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:19,360
任何东西都好过那些骑在马背上的祖先们
Anything's better than those gloomy ancestors on horseback.

326
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:20,704
你很早以前就音讯全无 
I'm so out of touch with you. 

327
00:27:20,704 --> 00:27:22,200
我都不知道你住在哪儿
I don't even know where you live.

328
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:24,200
我们住的地方离这就隔着三条街
Oh, we only live three streets away.

329
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:25,560
你们
We?

330
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:27,120
我和Armand
Armand and I.

331
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:28,345
看来我还有些事情不知道 
Something else I didn't know about you. 

332
00:27:28,345 --> 00:27:30,600
Armand是何许人也
What does Armand do?

333
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:32,181
他在夜总会里弹钢琴 
He plays piano in a nightclub, 

334
00:27:32,181 --> 00:27:34,360
所以我想你恐怕不会同意我俩在一起
so you probably won't approve.

335
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,280
- 你不是和那个谁...   - Daniel
- Weren't you with, erm...? - Daniel.

336
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:39,200
对 我挺喜欢Daniel的 他怎么了
Yes, I rather liked Daniel. What happened to him?

337
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,920
他遇到了一个卖蓝铃花的姑娘
A Bluebell girl happened.

338
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:43,960
这很荒唐 那姑娘比他还高4英寸
Which is absurd,she's four inches taller than he is.

339
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:47,440
所以你在Armand身上找慰藉
So you found solace in Armand?

340
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:52,000
比那正经多了
It's more serious than that.

341
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:56,800
你上次写信给我的时候你还在恋爱中呢
There was a lady in your life the last time you wrote to me.

342
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:58,760
我早跟你说了要去追求她
I told you to pursue her.

343
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,320
我追了
I did.

344
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:01,760
然后呢
And?

345
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,840
我想我已经失去她了
I think I may have lost her.

346
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,680
我是Anna Skarbek
Anna Skarbek.

347
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,360
是我
'It's me.'

348
00:28:24,360 --> 00:28:25,840
Jean-Francois 是你吗
Jean-Francois?

349
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:30,160
你怎么知道我在这儿
'How did you know I was here?'

350
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:33,600
我打电话给国际联盟  他们最终给了我你的号码
I called the League.They finally gave me a number.

351
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:36,600
- 你在哪儿   - 我在巴黎
- Where are you? - 'In Paris.'

352
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,040
我想接你过来住
I want you to live with me here.

353
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,560
我不能这么做
'I can't do that.

