00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:50,200
我从来都没真正弄明白你的工作到底是什么
I've never quite understood what it is.

528
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:51,560
这颜色适合我吗
Is this my colour?

529
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:58,400
当然
Of course it is.

530
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:02,080
我觉得你应该需要它
I thought you might need it.

531
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:03,880
我知道你怕冷
I know how you feel the cold.

532
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,880
他们会把它偷走的
They'll steal it.

533
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,400
不 他们不会
No, they won't.

534
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:14,104
你的那位军官朋友怎么样了  
How's your officer? 

535
00:41:14,104 --> 00:41:15,960
你说他不是波兰人
He's not Polish, you said.

536
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,560
法国人
French.

537
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:20,720
你那位法国人是位绅士吗
Your Frenchman's a gentleman?

538
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:30,640
他再也不是我的男人了
He's not my gentleman anymore.

539
00:41:59,767 --> 00:42:00,818
抱歉 请问你是谁
I'm sorry ,who are you?

540
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:02,984
我是Armand 钢琴演奏家 
I'm Armand. The piano player. 

541
00:42:02,984 --> 00:42:05,400
顺便说一句 你的钢琴该调一调音了
And yours needs tuning, by the way.

542
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:08,160
啊 你是Gabrielle的朋友
Oh, you're Gabrielle's friend.

543
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,080
不止如此 上校
A little more than that, Colonel.

544
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:15,880
你在这儿干嘛 为什么我不知道你要来
What are you doing here? Why didn't I know you were coming?

545
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:18,720
因为你一直找借口对我们避而不见
Because you'd have found some excuse not to see us.

546
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:21,040
你最近过得好吗
How are you?

547
00:42:21,040 --> 00:42:22,440
你看起来很糟糕
You look terrible.

548
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:33,640
James Joyce说
James Joyce said that

549
00:42:33,640 --> 00:42:38,160
爱尔兰是唯一一个从未迫害过犹太人的国家
Ireland is the only country that has never persecuted the Jews.

550
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,800
你知道为什么吗
Do you know why?

551
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:41,600
不知道 为什么
No, why?

552
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:44,600
因为他们不让犹太人入境
Because they never let them in!

553
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:51,480
越来越多的犹太人跑到巴黎来了
More and more Jewish people are coming to Paris.

554
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:53,661
很多人到我的店里来
Many of them come to my stall,

555
00:42:53,662 --> 00:42:56,280
试着卖些画和珠宝
trying to sell paintings, jewellery.

556
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:58,240
当他们变卖家当的时候 
And when they've sold them, 

557
00:42:58,240 --> 00:43:00,320
他们打算又何去何从呢
where do they plan to go? Hmm?

558
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:02,800
巴勒斯坦?  或是美国?
Palestine? America?

559
00:43:02,800 --> 00:43:05,240
我没有古董可卖
I don't have an art collection to sell.

560
00:43:05,240 --> 00:43:08,280
我想我可以在远洋轮船上弹钢琴
I guess I could always play piano on an ocean liner

561
00:43:08,280 --> 00:43:11,360
如果战争爆发 就在哈瓦那弃船登陆
if the war breaks out, jump ship in Havana.

562
00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:12,524
你可以到赌场里弹琴 
You could play in a casino 

563
00:43:12,524 --> 00:43:14,880
而我则做个卖香烟的女郎
and I'll be the cigarette girl.

564
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,320
老天啊 你们两个 严肃点儿
For God's sake, you two, be serious.

565
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:21,396
这种我们所拥有的 所热爱的生活 
This life we have, this life we love, 

566
00:43:21,396 --> 00:43:23,080
你们都认为是理所当然
you take for granted.

567
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:27,640
但这一切都会消散  就是那样
It could all vanish. Just like that.

568
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,360
那你有什么好建议呢
So what do you suggest?

569
00:43:33,440 --> 00:43:35,800
我们要每天都生活在对未来的恐惧中么
We live every day afraid of tomorrow?

570
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:38,120
我们就是这么熬过来的
That's how we were living.

571
00:43:38,120 --> 00:43:42,640
现在好一点了 多亏了你哥哥
A little less now, thanks to your brother.

572
00:43:42,640 --> 00:43:45,560
至少我们知道明天会是怎样
At least be aware of what tomorrow might be.

573
00:43:47,600 --> 00:43:50,440
人们表现的就好像最坏的境况永远不会发生
People act as though the worst will never happen.

574
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:52,360
这就是你的做法吧
That's just how you act yourself.

575
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,040
你怎么能这么说
How can you say that?

576
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:03,080
你什么都不做
You don't do anything about anything.

577
00:44:03,080 --> 00:44:06,040
除了喝遍父亲酒窖里的藏酒
Apart from drink your way through Father's cellar.

578
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:11,280
你觉得你父亲会介意我们 呃 再喝一瓶
Do you think your father would mind if we, er, drank another one?

579
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:14,360
请便
Help yourself.

580
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:24,400
恕我离席告退了
If you'll excuse me.

581
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:26,800
晚安
Good night.

582
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:29,080
- 晚安   - 晚安
- Good night.  - Good night.

583
00:45:30,320 --> 00:45:31,840
Emile看见了他们两个
Emile saw the pair of them.

584
00:45:31,840 --> 00:45:34,480
正在开车向南边草地的树林而去
Driving up to the woods above the south meadow.

585
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:36,080
就是你给我说过的那两个
The two you described to me.

586
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:42,960
你待在这儿
You stay here.

587
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:44,400
当然了 长官
Of course, sir.

588
00:45:55,360 --> 00:45:57,720
上校要上哪儿去
Where's the Colonel going?

589
00:45:57,720 --> 00:45:59,720
今天晚饭时我们就知道了
We'll find out at dinner tonight.

590
00:46:37,840 --> 00:46:39,640
我们需要铁锹
We need shovels.

591
00:46:44,200 --> 00:46:45,720
都怪我
I blame myself.

592
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:49,080
苏联方面知道你们在华沙联系的人是我
The Soviets knew it was me you approached in Warsaw.

593
00:46:49,080 --> 00:46:52,160
他们迟早会把这些联系起来的
They were bound to make the connection sooner or later.

594
00:46:52,160 --> 00:46:53,920
所以那些来的人...?
So these men who came...?

595
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:56,280
我都处理好了
I've dealt with that situation.

596
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:58,359
Fernand开他们的车去里昂了  
Fernand is driving their car to Lyon. 

597
00:46:58,359 --> 00:46:59,680
然后在某处弃车
He'll dump it somewhere.

598
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:00,880
那我们呢
And us?

599
00:47:02,040 --> 00:47:05,400
我昨晚已经和巴黎方面说过了 今早又谈了一次
I spoke to Paris last night and again this morning.

600
00:47:05,400 --> 00:47:06,990
你们将要前往布列塔尼
You're going to Brittany,

601
00:47:06,991 --> 00:47:09,600
显然 那是一个可爱的小山村 还靠着海
a pretty village, apparently, on the sea.

602
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:12,040
我会把你们送到巴黎
I'll drive you as far as Paris.

603
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:13,680
你也会一起离开么
You're leaving too?

604
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:17,280
是的  我妹妹说得对
Yes. My sister's right.

605
00:47:17,280 --> 00:47:19,400
我在这儿不问世事的时间够久了
I've been buried here for too long.

606
00:47:30,640 --> 00:47:32,120
我给你买了这个
I brought you these.

607
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:34,400
噢
Oh.

608
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:37,800
我还以为会是松露巧克力呢
I was rather hoping for truffles.

609
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:39,960
难道它们不是在你那一带出产的么
Don't they come from your neck of the woods?

610
00:47:39,960 --> 00:47:42,440
看起来你并不需要它们  你怎么了
You don't look like you need them. What was it?

611
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:46,680
胆结石  怎么就得上胆结石了
Gallstones. How on earth does one get gallstones?

612
00:47:46,680 --> 00:47:48,800
跟鹅肝和熟食打交道打了50年   
50 years of foie gras and charcuterie?  

613
00:47:48,800 --> 00:47:50,040
胡说
Rubbish.

614
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:51,600
你来这儿干什么
So why are you here?

615
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:55,360
我得去工作 将军
I need to go to work, General.

616
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:57,320
我得回归这场博弈
I need to get back in the game.

617
00:47:58,720 --> 00:48:01,480
最近 我们与波兰人在他们遭遇入侵的事件上
Recently, we reached an agreement with the Poles

618
00:48:01,480 --> 00:48:03,680
达成了共识
in the event of their being invaded.

619
00:48:03,680 --> 00:48:06,280
我们在讨论的是一项非常危险的任务
We're talking about a very dangerous mission.

620
00:48:06,280 --> 00:48:10,200
这关乎他们的国家主权与未来的长期生存
It's essential to their sovereignty and long-term survival.

621
00:48:10,200 --> 00:48:13,520
这件事目前只有若干最高级别的人知情
It's only known to a few at the highest possible level.

622
00:48:13,520 --> 00:48:16,200
我本来派了一个人两天后出发
I had a man leaving in two days.

623
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:20,080
但你更了解波兰人  你能代替他
But you know the Poles better. You can replace him.

624
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:21,560
多谢了
Thank you.

625
00:48:23,120 --> 00:48:24,391
我希望能够了解近几个月来
I'd like to see whatever

626
00:48:24,392 --> 00:48:27,040
你从Elter那里得到的情况 不论那是什么
you've received from Elter in the last few months.

627
00:48:27,040 --> 00:48:28,880
最近都是些无聊事
Rather dull reading recently,

628
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:31,560
不过我会和Lessard安排一下的
but I'll arrange it with Lessard.

629
00:48:31,560 --> 00:48:34,800
当你从华沙回来后 我就该出院了
And when you get back from Warsaw, I'll be out of this place

630
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:36,840
我们就可以享用一顿异常美好的午餐
and we can enjoy a really good lunch.

631
00:48:36,840 --> 00:48:38,360
你的医生同意么
Will your doctors allow it?

632
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:40,040
我才不邀请他们
I won't invite them.

633
00:48:43,800 --> 00:48:45,268
那么 你认为你可以从这儿找出
So, you think you can find

634
00:48:45,269 --> 00:48:47,640
一些被我们遗漏的东西 是么
things in here that we missed, is that it?

635
00:48:47,640 --> 00:48:48,981
并非如此  我只是想重新
Not at all. I just want to

636
00:48:48,982 --> 00:48:51,200
了解形式  已经有一段时间了
get back in the picture. It's been a while.

637
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:53,680
然而你却你就要去执行我等凡人
And yet you're off on a high-priority mission

638
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:55,960
眼中的最高优先级任务了
which is classified to us mere mortals.

639
00:48:55,960 --> 00:48:59,280
我了解波兰  我有线人和关系网
I know Poland. I have contacts and connections.

640
00:48:59,280 --> 00:49:01,840
并且Beauvilliers会支持你的
And Beauvilliers behind you.

641
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:04,200
如果战争爆发了任务便不会持续多长时间
That won't last long if war breaks out.

642
00:49:05,560 --> 00:49:07,080
你也说了是 如果
You still say "If".

643
00:49:23,400 --> 00:49:25,440
我在这儿安排了一场会议
I've set the meeting in here.

644
00:49:25,440 --> 00:49:28,440
你以前的公寓还是空的 所以你还可以住在那儿
Your old apartment's empty so you can stay there.

645
00:49:29,760 --> 00:49:31,720
不过 恐怕没有管家了
No housekeeper, I'm afraid.

646
00:49:31,720 --> 00:49:33,440
你能和我们待多久
How long will you be with us?

647
00:49:33,440 --> 00:49:35,120
也许是两天
Two days, perhaps.

648
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:38,240
噢 真可惜  没了你可就什么都不同了
Oh, what a shame. It's not the same without you.

649
00:49:38,240 --> 00:49:40,040
你后来和Anna联系了吗
Have you been in touch with Anna?

650
00:49:40,040 --> 00:49:41,880
目前她在纽约
She's in New York at the moment.

651
00:49:41,880 --> 00:49:43,154
纽约  天呐
New York! Goodness.

652
00:49:43,155 --> 00:49:46,240
国联在世界博览会上有一个展馆
The League has a pavilion at the World's Fair.

653
00:49:46,240 --> 00:49:48,720
噢 Mercier  阴魂不散 嗯?
Ah, Mercier! Couldn't stay away, huh?

654
00:49:48,720 --> 00:49:51,120
呃 你希望我在这场会议里出席么
Erm, do you want me to sit in on this meeting?

655
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:53,360
真谢谢你 那无关紧要
Thank you, that won't be necessary.

656
00:49:53,360 --> 00:49:56,280
啊 我知道  那么你没什么需要的了
Ah, I see. So there's nothing that you need?

657
00:49:56,280 --> 00:49:57,880
来杯咖啡还是很不错的
Coffee would be nice.

658
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:05,080
显然 德军会从西边进攻
Obviously the Germans will attack from the west,

659
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:07,880
所以我们的路线得是东南方 进入罗马尼亚
so our route has to be south-east, into Romania.

660
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:11,960
我们的外交部已经向布加勒斯特提议了
Our Foreign Ministry has already made overtures with Bucharest.

661
00:50:07,960 --> 00:50:11,960
{\pos(192,26)} Bucharest 罗马尼亚首都

662
00:50:11,960 --> 00:50:15,280
将会有一艘货轮出现在黑海的康斯坦察
There'll be a freighter at Constanza on the Black Sea.

663
00:50:15,280 --> 00:50:16,787
升着中立的旗子
It will fly a neutral flag

664
00:50:16,788 --> 00:50:19,280
但是配有法国船员和一艘武装的护卫舰
but have a French crew and an armed escort.

665
00:50:22,240 --> 00:50:24,800
货物经由马赛
It will take the consignment to Marseilles.

666
00:50:24,800 --> 00:50:26,880
最终抵达苏黎世
Ultimate destination - Zurich.

667
00:50:26,880 --> 00:50:30,400
我希望你是那个监守全程的人
I want you to be the person who sees it through.

668
00:50:30,400 --> 00:50:32,360
我会的
I'll insist on it.

669
00:50:32,360 --> 00:50:34,880
当然 我希望永远不要走到这一步
Of course, I hope it never comes to this.

670
00:50:34,880 --> 00:50:36,360
我们都知道这不可避免
We both know it will.

671
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,720
我上次在这儿的时候
When I was last here,

672
00:50:43,720 --> 00:50:45,573
我得到了一个促使我在
I got a tip that led to

673
00:50:45,574 --> 00:50:49,120
柏林的IN6里插入一个线人的暗示
me setting up an informant in IN6 in Berlin.

674
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:51,600
有什么想和我说的么
Anything to share with me?

675
00:50:51,600 --> 00:50:52,880
你不会想知道的
You wouldn't want it.

676
00:50:52,880 --> 00:50:55,640
在最后的两天我一直都在整理所有最新的材料
I've been over all the recent material in the last two days.

677
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:57,000
我认为材料有问题
I think it's tainted.

678
00:50:58,360 --> 00:50:59,880
Lapp博士在华沙么
Is Doctor Lapp in Warsaw?

679
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:01,120
他在  怎么了
He is. Why?

680
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:05,600
Lapp就是那个给了我暗示的人
It was Lapp who gave me the tip.

681
00:51:22,400 --> 00:51:26,280
恐怕自我们上次见面后
The world has not improved

682
00:51:26,280 --> 00:51:29,280
这世道仍旧一点儿都没改变
since we saw each other last, I fear.

683
00:51:30,840 --> 00:51:32,280
我在柏林见着你的时候
When I saw you in Berlin,

684
00:51:32,280 --> 00:51:34,920
我很感谢你那慎重的态度
I was grateful for your discretion.

685
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:39,560
如果战争爆发了
If war does break out,

686
00:51:39,560 --> 00:51:42,560
你将会理解我必须效忠自己的祖国
you will understand that I must serve my country,

687
00:51:42,560 --> 00:51:44,920
- 无论她的领导人是谁   - 当然
- whoever its leaders.  - Of course.

688
00:51:50,040 --> 00:51:53,000
我得感谢你帮我联系上了Halbach
I wanted to thank you for the Halbach connection.

689
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:54,560
据我所知 他是安全的
As far as I know, he's safe.

690
00:51:54,560 --> 00:51:56,400
是的 我听说了
Yes, I had heard that.

691
00:51:56,400 --> 00:51:59,200
然后你又去联系他了么
And did it lead you to his contact?

692
00:51:59,200 --> 00:52:01,200
还是说是我多嘴了
Or am I asking too much?

693
00:52:01,200 --> 00:52:03,240
我去了  他很有用
It did. He's been very useful.

694
00:52:04,920 --> 00:52:07,760
除了我觉着他已经暴露了
Except I think he's been exposed.

695
00:52:07,760 --> 00:52:09,080
投敌了
Turned.

696
00:52:10,280 --> 00:52:12,293
拿纳粹想让我们相信的东西来迷惑我们   
Feeding us what the Nazis want us to believe.  

697
00:52:12,293 --> 00:52:13,600
真的
Really?

698
00:52:14,960 --> 00:52:16,520
你为何如此判断
What makes you think so?

699
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:20,240
他情报的质量
The quality of his intelligence.

700
00:52:21,720 --> 00:52:24,600
你在柏林有着强大的关系网 博士
You have powerful connections in Berlin, Doctor.

701
00:52:25,720 --> 00:52:28,560
是否有可能证实我的怀疑?
Would it be possible to confirm my suspicions?

702
00:52:28,560 --> 00:52:31,400
- 这些都被第二局曝光了么   - 没有
- Are they shared by the Deuxieme Bureau?  - No.

703
00:52:28,560 --> 00:52:31,400
{\pos(192,26)} 法国第二局:法国情报机关

704
00:52:31,400 --> 00:52:33,240
目前为止我还没有走漏任何风声
So far I've kept this to myself.

705
00:52:33,240 --> 00:52:35,280
我建议你如此
I suggest you do,

706
00:52:35,280 --> 00:52:39,120
直到我完成一些调查
until I have made some enquiries.

707
00:52:39,120 --> 00:52:42,000
我会谨慎的 不过
I will be discreet, but...

708
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:44,800
我们都处在危险的边缘 你和我
we are on dangerous ground, you and I.

709
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:37,640
在我向Lapp博士吐露秘密后的不到几小时
A few hours after I confided in Doctor Lapp,

710
00:54:34,663 --> 00:54:35,863
{\pos(192,26)} 巴黎

711
00:54:37,640 --> 00:54:39,440
就有人进来想要杀我
someone came to kill me.

712
00:54:39,440 --> 00:54:42,160
所以我只能假设他是想我保持沉默
So I can only assume he was trying to silence me.

713
00:54:42,160 --> 00:54:44,880
如果我能成功说服我上司
If I convinced my superiors of my suspicions,

714
00:54:44,880 --> 00:54:47,960
那么Elter那条线对于纳粹来说将是无用的
then the Elter pipeline would be useless to the Nazis.

715
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:50,120
你认为Lapp让你出面
You think Lapp set you up in the first place

716
00:54:50,120 --> 00:54:52,560
- 去发现Elter的身份   - 我确信
- to discover Elter's identity?  - Convinced of it.

717
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:54,240
你让Pakulski逮捕他了么
Did you get Pakulski to arrest him?

718
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:57,440
没有证据  没人能逮捕他
There's no evidence. Nothing they can hold him on.

719
00:54:57,440 --> 00:54:59,800
并且 如果你知道了谁是你的敌人
Besides, if you know who your enemy is,

720
00:54:59,800 --> 00:55:02,040
有时最好让他处于活跃状态
it's sometimes best to keep him in play.

721
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:05,120
这真是个饱受摧残 扭曲了的间谍世界
What a tortured, twisted business this espionage is.

722
00:55:07,560 --> 00:55:09,680
你想除了胆结石之外再患上痛风吗
Do you want to add gout to gallstones?

723
00:55:10,920 --> 00:55:13,560
我在医院里时可都梦想着这些呢
I dreamed of this when I was in hospital.

724
00:55:16,200 --> 00:55:19,880
你认为Angela女士有多重要?
How seriously do you regard Lady Angela?

725
00:55:19,880 --> 00:55:23,040
她可能看起来比较轻浮 但她和丘吉尔身边的人
She may seem frivolous but she has very good connections

726
00:55:23,040 --> 00:55:25,080
保持着密切的联系
with people who have Churchill's ear.

727
00:55:25,081 --> 00:55:26,680
你能否把事情提到议案里
Can you put things in motion?

728
00:55:26,680 --> 00:55:28,200
噢 比你想象的要快多了
Oh, sooner than you think.

729
00:55:30,353 --> 00:55:32,323
{\pos(192,26)} 三国会议
注释:苏 英 法三国军备制定会议

730
00:55:33,213 --> 00:55:34,652
{\pos(192,26)} 1939年7月

731
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:34,960
- 我确信就是他   - 但是很明显
- I'm sure he is.  - But clearly,

732
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:37,320
- 在这一点上务必要谨慎考虑   - 是的
- discretion is called for at this point.  - Yes.

733
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:39,810
Mercier上校 
Colonel Mercier, 

734
00:55:39,810 --> 00:55:42,240
我来向你介绍Duff Cooper
I'd like to introduce Duff Cooper.

735
00:55:42,240 --> 00:55:45,000
你在这儿有着良好的声誉 上校
You have sympathetic ears here, Colonel.

736
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:48,280
这是我对于比利时的分析
This is my analysis of the Belgian scenario.

737
00:55:48,280 --> 00:55:49,837
虽然我应该加上一些
Though I should add that some

738
00:55:49,838 --> 00:55:52,200
我上司所不信任的东西
of my superiors don't give it much credence.

739
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:55,440
我们会再见的 上校 大概就在今晚稍晚的时候
We'll meet again, Colonel, possibly later tonight.

740
00:55:55,440 --> 00:55:57,160
我把这个留给你 Angela
I leave that to you, Angela.

741
00:56:05,840 --> 00:56:08,240
Duff是丘吉尔的私人秘书
Duff is Churchill's Private Secretary,

742
00:56:08,240 --> 00:56:10,960
所以你的报告是不会在托盘上摞着吃灰的
so your report won't gather dust in an in-tray.

743
00:56:10,960 --> 00:56:12,440
如果他们的反应良好
If they respond well,

744
00:56:12,440 --> 00:56:15,480
你可能就想横渡英吉利海峡继续调查了
you might want to follow this up with a trip across the Channel.

745
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,480
这任务不显得太繁重了么
Not too onerous a mission?

746
00:56:17,480 --> 00:56:20,520
乘午夜的卧铺和夫人前去伦敦
A midnight sleeper to London with Her Ladyship.

747
00:56:20,520 --> 00:56:23,480
我觉着如果我们飞去的话会更安全
I think it might be safer if we flew.

748
00:56:23,480 --> 00:56:26,320
顺便问一下 谁是那个守口如瓶的人
By the way, who was that man who didn't say anything?

749
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:27,081
他在我们的布局里  
He's in our game. 

750
00:56:27,081 --> 00:56:28,800
我记得他名字是Philby
I think his name's Philby.

751
00:56:55,640 --> 00:56:57,120
看到什么了
What is it?

752
00:57:16,960 --> 00:57:18,520
Max Mostov
Max Mostov!

753
00:57:20,280 --> 00:57:23,400
上帝啊  潇洒的中校
God in heaven! The dashing Colonel.

754
00:57:23,400 --> 00:57:25,480
英俊如昔啊
Handsome as ever, I see.

755
00:57:27,240 --> 00:57:30,640
我还以为你死了  或者进了集中营
I assumed you were dead. Or in a gulag.

756
00:57:30,640 --> 00:57:34,000
我很幸运  他们弄坏了我的指关节
I was fortunate. They gave me a rap on the knuckles,

757
00:57:34,000 --> 00:57:36,960
然后把我丢进了监狱里关了几个月
then threw me in jail for a few months.

758
00:57:36,960 --> 00:57:39,399
然后他们送你去巴黎休养生息?  
And then they send you to Paris to recuperate? 

759
00:57:39,399 --> 00:57:41,400
你这个骗子
You're a liar.

760
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:45,480
你是他们中的一员  你一直都是
You're one of theirs. You always were.

761
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:49,520
你骗过了所有人 我承认
You had us all fooled, I give you that.

762
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:51,623
你知道 当你一直都和
You know, when you are always

763
00:57:51,624 --> 00:57:54,960
根本不清楚你的真面目 或是从不知道
with people who don't know who you really are,

764
00:57:54,960 --> 00:57:59,320
你的秘密的那些人在一起时
who do not know that secret part of you,

765
00:57:59,320 --> 00:58:02,320
那会让你觉得 在某种程度上高人一等
it makes you feel, in a way, above them.

766
00:58:03,760 --> 00:58:05,680
你认为那是吸引力么
Do you think that's the appeal?

767
00:58:05,680 --> 00:58:07,720
那些对我来说毫无吸引力
Nothing about that appeals to me.

768
00:58:07,720 --> 00:58:11,040
过去的就过去了
Water under the bridge.

769
00:58:11,040 --> 00:58:13,720
这是我们两个之间的疯狂交易 嘿
This is a crazy business of ours, hey?

770
00:58:13,720 --> 00:58:15,600
看看我们
Look at us.

771
00:58:15,600 --> 00:58:17,880
现在我们可是并肩作战的战友
Now we are comrades in arms,

772
00:58:17,880 --> 00:58:21,840
苏联和法国联合起来共同反对可怕的希特勒
Soviets and French united against the dreaded Hitler.

773
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:26,520
我们应该为这个喝一杯
We should drink to this.

774
00:58:26,520 --> 00:58:28,640
我可不想与你共饮 Max
I don't want to drink with you, Max.

775
00:58:28,640 --> 00:58:29,960
请便
Suit yourself.

776
00:58:31,880 --> 00:58:36,200
我听说你和可爱的Anna处得可并不怎么好啊
I hear it did not go so well with you and the lovely Anna.

777
00:58:36,200 --> 00:58:38,640
她在你身上浪费了太多毫无意义的眼泪
She wasted a lot of pointless tears on you.

778
00:58:41,040 --> 00:58:42,840
我告诉你
And I tell you something.

779
00:58:44,280 --> 00:58:46,880
我会让她回心转意
I would have her back.

780
00:58:46,880 --> 00:58:48,520
易如反掌
Just like that!

781
00:59:02,280 --> 00:59:04,680
我想用我这双手亲手掐死他
I wanted to strangle him with my bare hands.

782
00:59:04,680 --> 00:59:07,800
之后我冷静下来并且意识到 我得告诉Anna
Then I calmed down and realised, I have to tell Anna.

783
00:59:07,800 --> 00:59:09,078
这将会使一切都变得不同   
It's going to make all the difference.  

784
00:59:09,078 --> 00:59:10,560
那你去了么
And have you?

785
00:59:10,560 --> 00:59:12,800
还没有  她还在从纽约回来的途中
Not yet. She's on her way back from New York.

786
00:59:12,800 --> 00:59:14,440
这是你生命中的真爱么
Is this the love of your life?

787
00:59:14,440 --> 00:59:16,800
我生命中的第二度挚爱
The second love of my life.

788
00:59:16,800 --> 00:59:17,707
Armand是我的第三个  
Armand's my third. 

789
00:59:17,707 --> 00:59:20,480
前两个真的算不上
The first two don't really count.

790
00:59:20,480 --> 00:59:21,760
谢了
Thank you.

791
00:59:21,760 --> 00:59:24,400
如果战争开始了 你们的爱情将会受到严峻的考验
Your love will be put to the test if there's a war.

792
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:26,000
因为Armand是个犹太人?
Because Armand's a Jew?

793
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:30,280
也许他应该坐船到哈瓦那
Maybe he should take that boat to Havana.

794
00:59:30,280 --> 00:59:33,120
他不会离开巴黎的  并且也不会离开我
He won't leave Paris. And he won't leave me.

795
00:59:33,120 --> 00:59:35,240
抱歉打断你们
Forgive the intrusion.

796
00:59:35,240 --> 00:59:36,760
我能加入你们一会吗
May I join you for a moment?

797
00:59:36,760 --> 00:59:38,200
当然可以 请坐
Of course, please.

798
00:59:38,200 --> 00:59:39,920
你想私下谈话吗
Do you want to talk in private?

799
00:59:39,920 --> 00:59:41,440
不 亲爱的
No, my dear.

800
00:59:41,440 --> 00:59:44,680
到早上整个世界就都会知道的
The whole world will know when it wakes up in the morning.

801
00:59:45,960 --> 00:59:47,367
第二局已经
The Deuxieme Bureau has

802
00:59:47,368 --> 00:59:50,120
拦截了德国大使馆的情报
picked up an intercept to the German Embassy.

803
00:59:51,480 --> 00:59:55,040
希特勒与斯大林签署了互不侵犯条约
Hitler has signed a non-aggression pact with Stalin.

804
00:59:55,040 --> 00:59:56,320
什么
What?

805
00:59:56,320 --> 00:59:58,960
两个相互抗衡了多年的人
Two men who vilified each other for years.

806
00:59:58,960 --> 01:00:01,680
他们会让Machiavell感到骄傲的
They'd make Machiavelli proud.

807
00:59:58,960 --> 01:00:01,680
{\pos(192,36)} 马基亚维利:意大利哲学家 《君主论》作者 
希特勒曾受其作品思想启发

808
01:00:01,680 --> 01:00:04,600
就在几天前 俄国人们还带着他们乏味的微笑和
Only days ago, the Russians were at that conference

809
01:00:04,600 --> 01:00:07,000
糟糕的西装出席了那次会议
with their bland smiles and bad suits.

810
01:00:07,000 --> 01:00:08,480
他们与我们签署了合约
They signed an agreement with us!

811
01:00:08,480 --> 01:00:09,982
这意味着什么
And what does this mean?

812
01:00:09,983 --> 01:00:12,800
这是一个卑鄙的 嘲讽的战术 这样俄国
It's a vile and cynical tactic so that Russia

813
01:00:12,800 --> 01:00:15,640
可以和德国一起瓜分波兰
and Germany can carve up Poland between them.

814
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:20,320
战争已无可避免 只是时间问题
War is inevitable, a matter of days.

815
01:00:20,320 --> 01:00:22,320
你们得尽快离开
You must leave as soon as possible.

816
01:00:29,006 --> 01:00:30,862
华沙

817
01:00:39,280 --> 01:00:40,850
噢 我亲爱的姑娘 
Oh, my dear girl, 

818
01:00:40,850 --> 01:00:43,920
波兰现在时局很糟糕 非常糟
what a terrible time for Poland, terrible.

819
01:00:43,920 --> 01:00:45,680
您怎么来了
What are you doing here?

820
01:00:45,680 --> 01:00:47,520
Mercier上校让我来接你
Colonel Mercier asked me to meet you.

821
01:00:47,520 --> 01:00:48,967
他大概一天之内会到华沙
He should be in Warsaw in

822
01:00:48,968 --> 01:00:51,400
他不顾一切地要见你
a day or so and he's desperate to see you.

823
01:00:51,400 --> 01:00:53,040
我不想看到他
I don't wish to see him.

824
01:00:54,880 --> 01:00:56,320
在你听了他让我告诉你的事情后
I think you might, my dear,

825
01:00:56,321 --> 01:00:58,720
你也许就不会这么想了
when you hear what he's asked me to tell you.

826
01:00:58,720 --> 01:01:00,120
是关于Max的
It's about Max.

827
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:22,760
Malka 我们会永远活在恐惧之中
Malka, we will always be afraid.

828
01:01:23,240 --> 01:01:28,240
无论是作为叛逃者还是犹太人
Either as defectors or Jews.

829
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:33,600
我们身边的都是陌生人
We live among strangers.

830
01:01:34,680 --> 01:01:37,800
不知道谁会第一个将矛头指向我们
Who knows who will be the first to point the finger?

831
01:01:39,728 --> 01:01:46,282
这样我们就能在一起了 永远在一起
This way we will be together, always.

832
01:02:12,320 --> 01:02:13,440
很高兴见到你 上校
Good to see you, Colonel.

833
01:02:13,440 --> 01:02:15,640
我也是 Marek 这边情况怎么样
You too, Marek. What's the mood here?

834
01:02:15,640 --> 01:02:18,800
所有40岁以下的人必须响应召集令
Everyone under 40 has to collect call-up papers.

835
01:02:18,800 --> 01:02:20,848
加上所有的预备役军人和退伍军人   
Plus all reservists and ex-soldiers. 

836
01:02:20,848 --> 01:02:21,800
你不是吗
Not you?

837
01:02:21,800 --> 01:02:24,640
上校想让我跟着你做这个任务
The Colonel wants me on this assignment you're on.

838
01:02:24,640 --> 01:02:27,040
他不会告诉我是什么
He won't tell me what it is.

839
01:02:38,880 --> 01:02:40,320
你要我做什么
What do you want from me?

840
01:02:40,320 --> 01:02:41,766
首先 从现在起
First, your silence about

841
01:02:41,767 --> 01:02:44,080
对你的一切所见所闻保持沉默
everything you see and hear from now on.

842
01:02:45,280 --> 01:02:47,800
我要你撤掉车厢内所有的座位
I need all the seats ripped out of those coaches

843
01:02:47,800 --> 01:02:50,480
车底板腾出位置来放板条箱
and the floorboards taken up to make room for some crates.

844
01:02:50,480 --> 01:02:55,120
明早之前我要车上恢复原状
Everything needs to be back in place by tomorrow morning.

845
01:02:55,120 --> 01:02:56,840
是军火吗
Is it ammunition?

846
01:02:56,840 --> 01:03:00,040
我是说 我要知道这个东西是不是随时会爆炸
I mean, I need to know if this thing could blow up at any minute.

847
01:03:00,040 --> 01:03:02,280
我不能告诉你是什么
I can't tell you what it is.

848
01:03:02,280 --> 01:03:04,240
我还要驾驶?
And I'm supposed to drive it?

849
01:03:04,240 --> 01:03:06,200
你不就是干这个的嘛
That's what you do, isn't it?

850
01:03:06,200 --> 01:03:07,880
干了40年了 没错
For 40 years, yes.

851
01:03:12,480 --> 01:03:14,280
这还是原定的计划吗
Was this the original plan?

852
01:03:16,240 --> 01:03:19,920
自从那些混蛋出其不意地占领我们之后 一切都变了
Everything's changed since those bastards took us by surprise.

853
01:03:19,920 --> 01:03:21,880
我们只得随机应对
We're improvising.

854
01:03:21,880 --> 01:03:23,760
我们什么时候走
So when will we leave?

855
01:03:23,760 --> 01:03:25,120
一大早走
Not before morning.

856
01:03:25,120 --> 01:03:26,640
我要去大使馆登记
I'll check in with the Embassy.

857
01:03:26,640 --> 01:03:30,200
噢 昨晚 厚脸皮出现在Cleo咖啡馆
Oh! Last night. Bold as brass in the Cafe Cleo.

858
01:03:30,200 --> 01:03:34,040
Lapp博士 以他的咖啡和法国白兰地 
Dr Lapp, with his coffee and his cognac, expressing his regret

859
01:03:34,040 --> 01:03:35,001
对发生在我们两个伟大的国家间的事情
that these things have

860
01:03:35,002 --> 01:03:36,880
表达了他的惋惜
come to pass between our two great nations.

861
01:03:36,880 --> 01:03:38,160
他还在这?
He's still here?

862
01:03:38,160 --> 01:03:39,440
是的
Yes.

863
01:03:55,840 --> 01:03:57,400
有什么消息
What have you heard?

864
01:03:57,400 --> 01:03:59,120
德国坦克向波兰进发
German tanks are heading for Poland.

865
01:03:59,120 --> 01:04:01,400
52个师 是150万人
52 divisions, that's a million and a half men.

866
01:04:01,400 --> 01:04:04,240
而斯大林在我们的东部边界有40个师
And Stalin has 40 divisions on our eastern border.

867
01:04:04,240 --> 01:04:07,320
他们会先炸飞机场 然后是电话局
They'll bomb the airfields first. Then telephone exchanges.

868
01:04:07,320 --> 01:04:08,400
你们什么时候离开
When will you get out?

869
01:04:08,400 --> 01:04:11,840
我们在等巴黎的消息 你一直都是对的
We're waiting for Paris to tell us. You were right all along.

870
01:04:13,080 --> 01:04:15,040
我要把这个给大使
I'll take this to the Ambassador.

871
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:18,528
Anna呢   
Anna? 

872
01:04:18,528 --> 01:04:21,200
我见过她了 我把Max的事告诉她了
I saw her. I told her about Max.

873
01:04:21,200 --> 01:04:22,400
然后?
And?

874
01:04:22,400 --> 01:04:23,880
震惊 流泪 悔恨
Shock. Tears. Regret.

875
01:04:25,200 --> 01:04:27,040
我要见她 她在哪
I have to see her. Where is she?

876
01:04:27,040 --> 01:04:29,920
她去乡下陪她母亲了
She went to the country to be with her mother.

877
01:04:29,920 --> 01:04:30,960
我知道地址
I have an address.

878
01:04:42,760 --> 01:04:45,440
为什么把我带到到这么可怕的地方
Why have I been brought to this dreadful place?

879
01:04:54,040 --> 01:04:56,280
你被指控为间谍 Lapp博士
You're accused of espionage, Dr Lapp.

880
01:04:56,280 --> 01:04:57,840
被谁指控的?
Accused by whom?

881
01:04:57,840 --> 01:04:58,880
Mercier上校
Colonel Mercier.

882
01:05:01,240 --> 01:05:03,240
太可恶了
That's outrageous.

883
01:05:03,240 --> 01:05:04,680
他没有证据
He has no evidence.

884
01:05:04,680 --> 01:05:05,880
我们不需要证据
We don't need evidence.

885
01:05:05,880 --> 01:05:07,720
我们并不是在监禁你
We are not arresting you.

886
01:05:07,720 --> 01:05:10,720
我们是根据紧急权力法拘留你
We are detaining you under the Emergency Powers Act.

887
01:05:10,720 --> 01:05:11,840
根本没有这种东西!
There's no such thing!

888
01:05:11,840 --> 01:05:13,280
这是我们将要被敌对外国势力
It's what we enact when we're

889
01:05:13,280 --> 01:05:15,840
入侵时颁布的法律
about to be invaded by a hostile foreign power.

890
01:05:15,840 --> 01:05:18,280
我要求跟我大使馆的人说话
I demand to speak to someone from my Embassy.

891
01:05:18,280 --> 01:05:20,680
您的要求我们会充分考虑的
Your demand is duly noted.

892
01:05:20,680 --> 01:05:22,960
现在 请给我您的腰带和鞋
Now, give me your belt and shoes.

893
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:34,560
那边还有多少
How many more of those are there?

894
01:05:34,560 --> 01:05:36,000
另外两货车的量
Another two truckloads.

895
01:05:43,600 --> 01:05:45,760
总重多少
What's the total weight?

896
01:05:45,760 --> 01:05:47,680
大约40,000千克
About 40,000 kilograms.

897
01:05:49,160 --> 01:05:52,800
这比塞满了人的火车还要重
That's more than the average train packed with passengers.

898
01:05:52,800 --> 01:05:53,886
我们不用很快的速度
We don't need to be fast,

899
01:05:53,887 --> 01:05:55,800
只要看起来像普通列车就行
we just need to look like an ordinary train.

900
01:06:37,166 --> 01:06:39,205
1939年 9月1日

901
01:06:40,394 --> 01:06:42,369
波兰 莫卡拉村

902
01:06:51,640 --> 01:06:53,640
睡着了吗
Did you sleep?

903
01:06:53,640 --> 01:06:55,440
几乎没有
Hardly.

904
01:06:55,440 --> 01:06:57,040
战争开始了
It's started.

905
01:06:57,040 --> 01:06:59,280
德国突击队已经越过边界
German commando units have crossed the border,

906
01:06:59,280 --> 01:07:02,480
他们有6个装甲师和8个机械化装备师的支援
backed up by six armoured and eight motorized divisions.

907
01:07:02,480 --> 01:07:04,480
上帝保佑 我们开战了
God preserve us, we're at war.

908
01:07:04,480 --> 01:07:06,016
我们可以来点你的苏格兰威士忌 
We could have some of your decent Scotch 

909
01:07:06,016 --> 01:07:08,560
如果还有的话
if there's any left.

910
01:07:08,560 --> 01:07:10,200
我会带着的
I'll bring it with me.

911
01:07:10,200 --> 01:07:11,920
走吧 车在外面
Let's go. Car's outside.

912
01:07:11,920 --> 01:07:13,862
安娜母亲的房子
Anna's mother's estate is

913
01:07:13,863 --> 01:07:17,280
离我们路线上的一个站只有30分钟的距离
just 30 minutes from a station on our route.

914
01:07:17,280 --> 01:07:18,520
那个地方叫博雷克
A place called Borek.

915
01:07:20,840 --> 01:07:22,760
我要去接她 在这里跟你碰面
I'm going to get her and meet you there.

916
01:07:22,760 --> 01:07:24,480
你不能去 你有命令在身
You are not. You have orders.

917
01:07:24,480 --> 01:07:26,200
Antoni 我只需要几个小时
I'm asking for a few hours, Antoni.

918
01:07:26,200 --> 01:07:28,800
拒绝请求 你知道我们要在这做什么
Request denied. You know what we have to do here.

919
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:31,040
我的正式任务是从罗马尼亚边界开始的
My official mission begins at the Romanian border.

920
01:07:31,040 --> 01:07:33,440
不 你正式任务从这里开始 就现在 跟我一起
No, your official mission begins here, now, with me.

921
01:07:33,440 --> 01:07:37,360
如果你危害任务 那么我们军事法庭上见
And if you jeopardise it, I'll see you are court-martialled.

922
01:07:37,360 --> 01:07:39,080
我会回到火车上的
I will make it back to the train.

923
01:07:43,560 --> 01:07:44,781
要是出了差错
If something goes wrong,

924
01:07:44,782 --> 01:07:46,920
你会被滞留在波兰中部
you'll be stranded in the middle of Poland

925
01:07:46,920 --> 01:07:49,520
俄国人和德国人会分别从两个方向攻进来
with Russians coming one way and Germans the other.

926
01:07:49,520 --> 01:07:53,080
死在爱人的怀里 这对你算是慰藉吗
So you die in your lover's arms, that will console you?

927
01:07:53,080 --> 01:07:54,440
我一定要去
I have to do this.

928
01:07:58,160 --> 01:08:00,840
Jean-Francois 你是我的朋友
Jean-Francois, you are my friend.

929
01:08:02,120 --> 01:08:04,240
我们是20年的朋友了
We've been friends for 20 years.

930
01:08:05,320 --> 01:08:07,096
但是 如果你没有出现在那个站 
But if you're not at that station, 

931
01:08:07,096 --> 01:08:09,160
我一分钟都不会等
I won't wait even a minute.

932
01:08:11,080 --> 01:08:12,360
我明白
I understand.

933
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:09,360
这些孩子从哪来的
Where did these children come from?

934
01:09:09,360 --> 01:09:12,880
从城里来的 母亲 对他们而言这里更安全
From the city, Mother. It's safer for them here.

935
01:09:14,760 --> 01:09:17,640
我过去很喜欢仆人的小孩玩闹的声音
I used to love the sound of the servants' children

936
01:09:17,640 --> 01:09:19,040
当这房子还是我们的时候
when the house was ours.

937
01:09:22,240 --> 01:09:25,280
有时他们会忘记给我们做午餐
Sometimes they forget about our lunch.

938
01:09:25,280 --> 01:09:27,320
大部分护士都离开了
Most of the nurses have left.

939
01:09:31,880 --> 01:09:35,640
现在是战争时期 妈妈 战争已经开始了
We're at war, Mother. It's started.

940
01:09:38,000 --> 01:09:42,000
我的两个兄弟在上一次战争中死去
My two brothers died in the last one.

941
01:09:42,000 --> 01:09:43,120
Patryk那时只有18岁
Patryk was only 18.

942
01:09:46,240 --> 01:09:48,920
但他们说再也不会有下一次战争了
But they said there would never be another one.

943
01:09:51,560 --> 01:09:53,200
昨天的汤是凉的
The soup was cold yesterday.

944
01:10:37,640 --> 01:10:39,640
你来这干嘛
What are you doing here?

945
01:10:39,640 --> 01:10:41,240
我来接你 Anna
I've come for you, Anna.

946
01:10:43,560 --> 01:10:46,440
你在内疚与泪水中荒废了一年
You wasted a year on guilt and tears.

947
01:10:46,440 --> 01:10:50,160
我们生命中本该共度的一年
A year of our lives we should have spent with each other.

948
01:10:51,600 --> 01:10:55,840
我当初多么愚蠢 我全都相信了
What a stupid woman I was. I believed it all.

949
01:10:55,840 --> 01:10:58,680
我本以为Max是需要拯救的灵魂
I thought Max was a soul that needed saving.

950
01:10:58,680 --> 01:11:02,120
那都是欺骗你的 我一直很想念你
It was all a deception. I've missed you.

951
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:12,560
你最好还是把我引见给你的母亲吧
You'd better introduce me to your mother.

952
01:11:27,560 --> 01:11:28,549
妈妈 
Mother, 

953
01:11:28,549 --> 01:11:31,720
这是Jean-Francois Mercier上校
this is Colonel Jean-Francois Mercier.

954
01:11:33,800 --> 01:11:35,800
荣幸之至 女士
An honour, Ma'am.

955
01:11:35,800 --> 01:11:38,120
的确是个绅士
A gentleman indeed.

956
01:11:38,120 --> 01:11:40,400
你能来拜访我们真是太好了
How kind of you to come and visit us.

957
01:11:40,400 --> 01:11:41,720
没有别人这样做过
No-one else ever does.

958
01:11:43,200 --> 01:11:44,920
我要你们跟我一起走
I want you both to come with me.

959
01:11:45,960 --> 01:11:47,880
- 去哪?   - 离开波兰
- Where to?   - Out of Poland.

960
01:11:47,880 --> 01:11:51,240
我们得赶上20千米外的一趟火车
We have to pick up a train 20 kilometres from here.

961
01:11:51,240 --> 01:11:54,240
所以越快越好 带的东西越少越好
So be as quick as you can, take as little as you need.

962
01:11:54,240 --> 01:11:58,360
你来自巴黎?  我喜爱我们住在巴黎的日子
Are you from Paris?  I loved it when we lived in Paris.

963
01:11:58,360 --> 01:12:00,360
我们住在那家有名的面包店旁
We were near that famous bakery.

964
01:12:00,360 --> 01:12:03,040
妈妈 您听到上校说的了 我们得离开了
Mother, you heard the Colonel. We have to leave.

965
01:12:03,040 --> 01:12:04,800
我没有去巴黎穿的衣服
I don't have the clothes for Paris.

966
01:12:04,800 --> 01:12:08,440
又是新的潮流了 可你必须要走 Anna
It will be all new fashions. You must go, Anna.

967
01:12:09,440 --> 01:12:11,600
不行 我不会把你留在这的
No! I won't leave you here.

968
01:12:11,600 --> 01:12:13,640
但你应该这么做
But you should.

969
01:12:14,680 --> 01:12:15,720
你恋爱了
You're in love.

970
01:12:20,680 --> 01:12:22,280
你还有大好青春
You have a life ahead of you.

971
01:12:25,080 --> 01:12:26,200
而我已风烛残年
Mine's behind me.

972
01:13:12,720 --> 01:13:15,200
我看见火车的烟了 看那边
I can see smoke. Look!

973
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:49,840
我们要减速吗
Do we slow down?

974
01:13:49,840 --> 01:13:51,400
如果他不在就不用了
Not if he's not there.

975
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:01,960
他没有停
He's not stopping!

976
01:14:20,840 --> 01:14:25,720
那辆车 是他的车 上校
The car. It's the car, Colonel.

977
01:14:44,520 --> 01:14:45,680
上校?
Colonel?

978
01:14:47,720 --> 01:14:49,360
刹车!
Hit the brakes!

979
01:15:12,240 --> 01:15:13,480
你时间掐得很紧
You cut it fine.

980
01:15:13,480 --> 01:15:15,840
谢天谢地 我有一辆法国车
Thank God I had a French car.

981
01:15:15,840 --> 01:15:16,880
很高兴见到你 Anna
Good to see you, Anna.

982
01:15:19,200 --> 01:15:20,240
好了 走吧
OK, let's go.

983
01:15:53,640 --> 01:15:55,166
我们正在前往边界 
We're heading for the border. 

984
01:15:55,166 --> 01:15:58,880
你 Pakulski 还有武装护卫
You, Pakulski, armed guards.

985
01:15:58,880 --> 01:15:59,920
怎么回事
What's going on?

986
01:16:02,200 --> 01:16:03,600
我们有一批隐蔽的货物
We have a hidden cargo.

987
01:16:05,440 --> 01:16:06,480
在我们脚下?
Under our feet?

988
01:16:08,880 --> 01:16:10,280
是什么?
What is it?

989
01:16:15,240 --> 01:16:18,880
我们正在疏散波兰全部的国家金银储备
We're evacuating the entire Polish national bullion reserve.

990
01:16:20,040 --> 01:16:22,440
抢在纳粹染指之前
Before the Nazis can get their hands on it.

991
01:16:24,560 --> 01:16:25,640
黄金?
Gold?

992
01:16:27,560 --> 01:16:31,240
40箱 每箱10锭
40 cases. 10 ingots in every case.

993
01:16:33,520 --> 01:16:35,400
-送到罗马尼亚?   -还有更远的地方
-To Romania? -And beyond.

994
01:17:09,160 --> 01:17:11,720
我是Vladimir Herschensohn
Vladimir Herschensohn.

995
01:17:12,960 --> 01:17:17,440
波兰国家交响乐团的首席小提琴手
Principal violinist of the Polish National Symphony Orchestra.

996
01:17:17,440 --> 01:17:19,000
我是Roman Kosinksi
Roman Kosinksi.

997
01:17:19,000 --> 01:17:21,200
噢 是学生?
Oh, a student?

998
01:17:21,200 --> 01:17:24,640
原来是 现在我都不知道自己是什么了
I was. Now I've no idea what I am.

999
01:17:24,640 --> 01:17:27,520
而且我可能再也见不到我的家人了
And I may never see my family again.

1000
01:17:27,520 --> 01:17:29,920
你要相信你会见到他们的
You must believe that you will.

1001
01:17:29,920 --> 01:17:32,120
相信他们会活下来 你自己也会活下来
That they will survive and so will you.

1002
01:17:33,800 --> 01:17:36,840
脊髓灰质炎你都幸免于难了
You survived polio.

1003
01:17:39,400 --> 01:17:42,440
我们是朝罗马尼亚的方向去吗
Is it true we are headed for Romania?

1004
01:17:42,440 --> 01:17:43,720
他们是这么说的
So they say.

1005
01:17:43,720 --> 01:17:46,200
我有表亲住那
Ah, I have cousins there.

1006
01:17:46,200 --> 01:17:48,560
他们有个不错的管弦乐队
They have a fine orchestra.

1007
01:17:48,560 --> 01:17:53,480
如果他们不接纳我 我就只能在街头卖艺了
If they won't have me, it will mean a cap on the pavement.

1008
01:18:00,400 --> 01:18:02,880
你会回去打仗吗 上校
Will you go back to fight this war, Colonel?

1009
01:18:05,320 --> 01:18:06,400
我们俩都会
We both will.

1010
01:18:21,353 --> 01:18:21,991
怎么了?

1011
01:18:21,991 --> 01:18:23,519
你没听见早些时候的爆炸声吗?

1012
01:18:23,519 --> 01:18:24,738
我们的军队已经很近了

1013
01:18:25,621 --> 01:18:26,757
守卫都走了

1014
01:18:27,535 --> 01:18:28,403
我们能出去了

1015
01:18:47,000 --> 01:18:48,920
停下来 别跑
Stop! Stop!

1016
01:18:50,365 --> 01:18:51,142
别开枪

1017
01:18:51,940 --> 01:18:52,526
我们是德国人

1018
01:18:52,526 --> 01:18:53,300
德国人!

1019
01:18:53,440 --> 01:18:55,720
谢谢你们告诉我们 我们是波兰人
Good of you to let us know. We're Polish.

1020
01:19:56,080 --> 01:19:57,320
怎么了
What's happening?

1021
01:19:57,320 --> 01:19:58,520
那有个女孩
There's a girl.

1022
01:20:04,880 --> 01:20:05,920
怎么了
What's happened?

1023
01:20:07,120 --> 01:20:09,640
我不确定 你待在这
I'm not sure, stay here.

1024
01:20:09,640 --> 01:20:10,680
你们两个跟我来
You two with me.

1025
01:20:15,520 --> 01:20:16,800
来 拿着这个
Here, take this.

1026
01:20:22,160 --> 01:20:23,960
我不知道这个怎么用
I don't know how to use this.

1027
01:20:24,960 --> 01:20:29,000
我来教你 我并不总是在拉小提琴的
I'll show you. I didn't always play the violin.

1028
01:20:32,240 --> 01:20:33,720
上去
Get in.

1029
01:20:35,840 --> 01:20:38,280
有问题吗
Is something wrong?

1030
01:20:38,280 --> 01:20:40,240
求你了 阁下
Please, Excellency.

1031
01:20:44,520 --> 01:20:46,280
带我一起走
Take me with you.

1032
01:20:48,160 --> 01:20:51,720
待在这 不要忘了金条
Stay here, don't leave the bullion.

1033
01:20:51,720 --> 01:20:53,880
我去看看发生什么了
I'm going to see what's happening.

1034
01:20:59,800 --> 01:21:01,200
你不用付我钱的
You don't have to pay me.

1035
01:21:01,200 --> 01:21:03,600
你住在哪 你的家人呢
Where do you live? Where is your family?

1036
01:21:03,600 --> 01:21:04,800
都走了
Gone.

1037
01:21:18,880 --> 01:21:20,520
我不会说你们的话
I don't speak your language.

1038
01:21:28,600 --> 01:21:29,760
你是谁
Who are you?

1039
01:21:29,760 --> 01:21:31,480
我在铁路公司工作
I work for the railroad.

1040
01:21:31,480 --> 01:21:33,830
你看起来不像铁路工人啊
You don't look like railroad worker.

1041
01:21:33,831 --> 01:21:35,920
火车上有什么值钱的东西吗
Anything valuable on this train?

1042
01:21:35,920 --> 01:21:38,040
只有人 去往边界
Just people, heading for the border.

1043
01:21:39,240 --> 01:21:41,360
逃跑哈?
Running, huh?

1044
01:21:41,360 --> 01:21:42,640
为什么不呢
Why not?

1045
01:21:42,640 --> 01:21:44,040
波兰人完蛋了
The Poles are finished.

1046
01:22:01,360 --> 01:22:02,720
你想要什么
What do you want from us?

1047
01:22:02,720 --> 01:22:05,640
钱 珠宝 女人
Money. Jewellery. Women.

1048
01:22:06,840 --> 01:22:09,760
别担心 丑的我们不要
Don't worry, we won't take ugly ones.

1049
01:22:09,760 --> 01:22:10,840
把那块表给我
Give me that watch.

1050
01:22:21,160 --> 01:22:23,480
你在铁路公司上班怎么可能有这个
You don't get this working for railroad.

1051
01:22:24,920 --> 01:22:26,440
你看那下面干什么
What do you see down there?

1052
01:23:14,560 --> 01:23:15,600
你还好吗
Are you all right?

1053
01:23:15,600 --> 01:23:18,520
还好 还有两个在车厢里
Fine. There's two more back in the carriage,

1054
01:23:18,520 --> 01:23:19,920
他们走不了了
they're not going anywhere.

1055
01:23:19,920 --> 01:23:22,160
对不起 他们逼我的
I'm sorry. They make me.

1056
01:23:47,720 --> 01:23:50,880
为什么我们不在野外的小屋定居下来
Why don't we settle in a cabin in the wild -

1057
01:23:50,880 --> 01:23:54,280
一口井 养几只山羊
a well, a few goats

1058
01:23:54,280 --> 01:23:56,000
远离这场战争
and hundreds of miles from the war?

1059
01:23:58,920 --> 01:24:01,480
我还要几只狗 几本书
I'd need dogs. And some books.

1060
01:24:02,920 --> 01:24:03,960
还有一个好酒窖
And a good cellar.

1061
01:24:05,040 --> 01:24:07,440
我还会学会缝纫
And I'd learn to sew.

1062
01:24:07,440 --> 01:24:09,880
我们到哪了
Where are we anyway?

1063
01:24:09,880 --> 01:24:12,040
明天我们会抵达边界
We'll reach the border tomorrow.

1064
01:24:12,040 --> 01:24:13,160
然后?
And then?

1065
01:24:14,440 --> 01:24:16,360
我不会再让你离开我的视线
I'll never let you out of my sight.

1066
01:24:19,400 --> 01:24:22,760
可能四到五周内到法国 我们就结婚
Could be in France in four or five weeks, we'll get married.

1067
01:24:24,000 --> 01:24:26,760
如果你要我成为一个体面的女人
If you want to make a respectable woman of me,

1068
01:24:26,760 --> 01:24:28,360
恐怕太晚了
I'm afraid you're too late.

1069
01:24:29,560 --> 01:24:30,600
我还可以试试
I can still try.

1070
01:25:41,480 --> 01:25:43,080
跟预想的一样
Looks like we're expected.

1071
01:25:44,160 --> 01:25:46,048
如果跟罗马尼亚人的交涉得不错的话 
If it goes well with the Romanians, 

1072
01:25:46,048 --> 01:25:47,320
之后的就全由你做主了
the rest is up to you.

1073
01:25:54,400 --> 01:25:57,120
退一步说 未来充满了不确定
The future is uncertain, to say the least.

1074
01:25:57,120 --> 01:26:00,040
无论发生什么 你们俩要共同面对
Whatever it may be, you two face it together.

1075
01:26:56,920 --> 01:26:58,440
现在该怎么办
What now?

1076
01:26:58,440 --> 01:27:00,360
竭尽所能活下来
We do our best to stay alive.

1077
01:27:31,906 --> 01:27:36,410
1939年12月 
150万德国军队涌入波兰

1078
01:27:39,088 --> 01:27:43,691
波兰的黄金储备经过罗马尼亚
通过土耳其和黎巴嫩
于10月到达巴黎

1079
01:27:45,399 --> 01:27:50,275
战争结束时
800,00华沙人死去
90%的老城成为废墟

